dublin_core.dcvalue: The objective of the study was to estimate the costs and health benefits of a public awareness campaign aimed at shortening the delay for thrombolytic therapy in patients with acute myocardial infarction AMI and to estimate the incremental costs and benefits of an additional telemedicine program
International journal of technology assessment in health care
Cost-effectiveness of interventions to reduce the thrombolytic delay for acute myocardial infarction.
